cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to improve the quality of photographs taken in low-light conditions using handheld smartphone cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks for joint denoising and deblurring, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper involves generating realistic short-long exposure image pairs, which can be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics). The use of simulated data for training the network also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
